news.title: Tax payers' body moves Andhra Pradesh HC against property tax system
news.para: Sunkara Rajendra Prasad, the counsel for the tax paying body, said capital value is released only when someone sells his or her property.

news.title: Acted against 588 buildings in municipalities: Gujarat government to HC
news.para: In an affidavit, the urban development urban housing department said it will place details of buildings in municipal corporation areas with regard to fire NOCs after the corporations send them the data. It placed details with regard to enforcement of fire safety rules in municipalities.

news.title: Chandigarh administration stops mention of house floor in bank NOCs
news.para: Earlier, estate office staff mentioned floor while issuing NoC to bank. According to the latest order, this is against the letter and spirit of the estate law of Chandigarh.

news.title: Gurugram: Four teams to speed up takeover of 11 private colonies
news.para: Each team comprises an executive engineer, assistant engineer and junior engineer. The teams will survey the colonies and prepare cost estimates for completing deficient infrastructural work.

news.title: SC asks Gujarat government to frame scheme on transfer of plots allotted to MPs, MLAs
news.para: The bench was hearing an interim application of an MLA, represented by lawyer Saurav Mishra, that the earlier order of the court be modified to permit allottees to transfer the property if the motive is not to earn profits.

news.title: Mumbai: Pay property tax dues via mobile, online modes now
news.para: Property tax bills have been made live on BMC Property Tax Portal. Payment may be done online using the payment gateway method.

news.title: Gr​eater Noida development body offers nine plots for commercial purpose
news.para: Application forms can be downloaded from the GNIDA website till October 8 and the last date for submitting them is October 12. The plots will be auctioned on October 25.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP razes 10 illegal floors, 12 shops in DLF-3
news.para: According to DTCP officials, this is the first time that such major action has been taken against illegal buildings in a residential block of the upscale licensed colony. Unauthorised construction has been a major concern for many DLF-3 residents for over a decade now.

news.title: Moratorium under IBC applies only to corporate debtor not to its promoters: SC
news.para: A bench of Justices DY Chandrachud, Vikram Nath and Hima Kohli allowed the home buyers to move against the promoters of the first respondent Corporate Debtor (Today Homes and Infrastructure Pvt Ltd), even though a moratorium has been declared under Section 14 of the IBC.

news.title: Brazil eases financing for low-income home buyers
news.para: The measures, which will take effect in about 60 days, are aimed at increasing access to affordable housing and boosting economic growth with more support for civil construction.

news.title: Royalty hike on marble, granite upsets tiles industry
news.para: As per the new order, royalty for marble slabs and tiles increased to Rs 500 from Rs 430 per tonne. Royalty on granite blocks having more than 70 cm dimension went up from Rs 215 to Rs 300 and from sizes less than 70 cm, the rate will be Rs 150 instead of Rs 90 per tonne.

news.title: SBI announces various offers for home loan borrowers
news.para: With the introduction of the new offer, a borrower can now avail home loan for any amount at a rate as low as 6.70 per cent, the bank said in a release.

news.title: Vadodara civic body to get Rs 167 crore towards land for bullet train project
news.para: NHSRCL is set to acquire land from VMC on the alignment for the bullet train. The alignment of the train traverses through the city from Chhani on one end and to Maneja on the other.

news.title: No homestay permitted in Nilgiris district: Madras HC
news.para: ​​Till a plan is put in place upon appropriate studies being conducted and a viable scientific report being obtained, no further permission for homestays in the Nilgiris should be granted, the court ruled.

news.title: Hyderabad: What ban? Illegal structures overrun all GO 111 villages
news.para: This despite a ruling by the National Green Tribunal (NGT) staying all activity in this no-construction belt spread over 84 villages which fall in the catchment area of two of Hyderabad’s biggest fresh water lakes - Osmansagar and Himayatsagar.
